rComments: The online class was great for me. Exams were at the University which was way better than the online exams I have this semester for child psychology. She posted material weeks in advance which gave you a chance to get ahead. The professor was very accessible outside class and always there to help her students.
Elle cherche à mettre une cohésion de groupe sur un cours en ligne, pas génial. Ça permet de ne pas prendre du retard dans les lectures.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: I would rather read the textbook than attend her lectures. She's always reading off of the slides or her notebook when she lectures. It is quite annoying actually, because it is harder to understand and take notes. However, if you don't understand something or have a question, she is always there to explain it in greater detail with examples.

Cramming information is essential for exams. Tests included lots of 'meticulous' and 'small detail' information found in the textbook and slides. Study everything in detail to pass. Textbook is essential. Extra credit assignment was given (thankfully). Otherwise, peppy and upbeat professor who is enthusiastic about her subject!

Very clear when explaining things, does her best to simplify things. Always asks if we understand, if not she'll try explaining it a different way. If you study and attend class, you'll do well on the exams. Very fair tests, always to give partial points and boost marks. English is second language but she speaks nearly perfectly.

very difficult to understand her speaking as she has a thick accent and ends most sentences with an upward inflection which is at the most annoying frequency, the only benefit is that you can skip every class and just read the textbook... however with the amount of psych profs i would highly recommend switching out

Gives very fair exams with no convoluted wording. She is very clear in class on what to expect for the exams-- there have been at least two times on tests there were exact sentences from the power points and textbook. the textbook and power points also work very well together. also get 4% for participating in experiments.
